Text.Value: Oh, but we couldn't accept your money for nothing -
Ah, so I see. Are we expecting anyone, Cora?
I don't know why he ran. Coward.
I bet that'll draw quite the crowd in a city like this.
I am Cora Highberry, and this is my husband, Roger. Delighted to meet you.
I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].  And you are?
If times are tough, I'm happy to donate. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
I don't know, Roger... We were just talking about the city being unsafe - and what of the children? If there's even the slightest chance -
Nothing, Cora? All the work you put in with the little ones is hardly nothing. Thank you, any help we can get is a blessing.
Me too, my love. Me too.
Well, how odd.
You're on a list of murder targets. Cora. I was protecting you.
I must say, if this a practical joke, it's of distinctly poor taste.
More than delighted! A little extra company's always welcome as we enter our twilight years - yet another reason we're putting on the wine festival!
Cora, my dear, who would really take the time our of their day to harm us?
I think Master Meztli was keen for us to try his wine. Speak with him if you wish to join us.
The festival was put together to raise funds for the children, you see. Times are a touch tough at the moment.
Perhaps he left the stove on.
Besides - if they try, well, I've got some life in me yet.
Why, whatever was the matter with that man? Why did he take off so quickly?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node will only enter the first time we try to speak with the highberrys after saving cora in perfect stealth

Text.Value: A wine festival sounds charming.
Which children are you raising money for?
You're welcome to stay a while if you like. Does us good to have a little extra life in the house.
Perhaps a small donation would help salve those scars? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Just a stranger - and a lost one at that. I'll show my way out.
Soon you are to be sacrificed, little lambs. You are on Father Bhaal's naughty list.
Yes, I suppose so... Doesn't explain all the shouting though.
I am so glad that monster was stopped.
We're lucky to be blessed with a rather spacious one - seems cruel to let it go unused if there are children in need.
Young Molly and Timothy, who we've recently taken charge of. Their parents... Well. War leaves the nastiest scars.
I'll let you get on with your day.
It's very kind of you to take orphans into your home.
Lovely to meet you, but I really must be going.
And of course, the Wine Festival itself is but a few days away - Cora, we do forget ourselves! We've not even asked this fine young stranger's name.
Roger, look, a visitor!
But do be careful if you're out and about - city's just not as safe as it used to be.
It is so lovely to see more young folk around the place. Really is.
Orphans? Ew. I've heard enough.
I'm sorry, Mrs Highberry, but you're on a list of murder targets. You're not safe here.
We hope so, it's going to be right on our doorstep!
I still can't believe... why would anyone want to kill... me? Th-thank you for saving us...
No - the grocer's just been, as has the chandler. Then there's your tailor - he's due soon to get the children outfitted for the festival...
I should probably get going.
'Another' reason? Why else would you run a wine festival?

Synopsis: Dialogue between the players and the Highberrys (both, alive) in the Serial Killer situation. There are the first victims. A flag signal the dialogue happens before Dolor appears and other flag if Dolor is killed and the couple survives.
